 when he comes in contact with a human being,

64
00:07:14,543 --> 00:07:19,091
what he learns, is full devotion.

65
00:07:19,882 --> 00:07:26,959
 It means, devotion is innately born within us.

66
00:07:30,190 --> 00:07:37,891
The seed of devotion is beforehand completely sown within us.

67
00:07:38,794 --> 00:07:44,225
 When we were not in this state, not in the human state

68
00:07:44,264 --> 00:07:48,950
 the emergence of devotion was more at that time.

69
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:53,536
Devotion set its roots deeply in us.

70
00:07:53,561 --> 00:07:56,750
 Take an example of any animal.

71
00:07:57,571 --> 00:07:59,585
You get a little love from him,

72
00:07:59,610 --> 00:08:02,966
 give him a little love, a little fondness for him

73
00:08:03,134 --> 00:08:08,643
 he gets so close to you, gives his regard to you

74
00:08:09,232 --> 00:08:13,037
 and in this way loves you.

75
00:08:13,502 --> 00:08:16,310
You must have heard about a horse too

76
00:08:16,510 --> 00:08:21,279
 that when a horse's rider falls down

77
00:08:21,304 --> 00:08:26,220
 or is about to die, he remains loyal to him.

78
00:08:33,920 --> 00:08:40,705
In the same way it is said about elephants.

79
00:08:42,416 --> 00:08:46,435
 The elephants' determination too is terrific.

80
00:08:46,460 --> 00:08:53,511
They never put their master to any trouble

81
00:08:54,090 --> 00:09:06,680
 and if a lion or any other animal attacks their master

82
00:09:06,705 --> 00:09:09,719
 the elephant will better die while going on fighting

83
00:09:10,156 --> 00:09:13,096
 but he will not allow his master to be touched.

84
00:09:13,354 --> 00:09:22,646
This relation of a master and superior and high-quality animals

85
00:09:24,312 --> 00:09:29,127
 this relation is established within us beforehand.

86
00:09:30,596 --> 00:09:36,493
And along with this relationship we get that power as well.

87
00:09:36,731 --> 00:09:38,316
 For example, I told you that

88
00:09:38,341 --> 00:09:41,035
 the elephant will die while going on fighting in the battlefield.

89
00:09:41,060 --> 00:09:45,415
The elephant gets this power of fighting too

90
00:09:45,440 --> 00:09:48,842
 because of his love and devotion.

91
00:09:53,368 --> 00:10:03,276
We say that Sahaj yoga is the work of love and Divine love is true.

92
00:10:03,522 --> 00:10:09,320
 But while doing this work, that power is also inherent in it.

93
00:10:12,347 --> 00:10:16,933
We may or may not know it,

94
00:10:18,986 --> 00:10:23,722
 we may or may not have any knowledge of that

95
00:10:23,949 --> 00:10:29,898
 but that also is inherent in it, and that is Divine power.

96
00:10:32,728 --> 00:10:37,319
Man's bowing down before anyone

97
00:10:37,419 --> 00:10:42,785
 to respect anyone, to consider anyone great

98
00:10:42,844 --> 00:10:46,081
 all these are the indications of that.

99
00:10:46,423 --> 00:10:53,321
But when he respects his master, then within him

100
00:10:53,543 --> 00:10:56,443
there is importance to his master

101
00:10:56,468 --> 00:11:01,285
 but along with that is his power as well.

102
00:11:01,712 --> 00:11:05,342
So, devotion and power are not two different things.

103
00:11:05,391 --> 00:11:08,058
 They are just one and the same.

104
00:11:08,083 --> 00:11:12,426
We will say that if there is power in the right hand

105
00:11:12,451 --> 00:11:14,295
 there is devotion in the left hand.

106
00:11:15,399 --> 00:11:18,065
This fusion of power and devotion

107
00:11:18,360 --> 00:11:23,236
 has been described beautifully in Shree Hanumanji.

108
00:11:25,049 --> 00:11:28,981
On the one hand He went burn Ravan's Lanka

109
00:11:30,412 --> 00:11:35,742
and there only He prostrated before Sitaji.

110
00:11:37,048 --> 00:11:42,223
 And when Sitaji said ''No, you are My son

111
00:11:42,319 --> 00:11:44,438
 I will not come at the behest of My son.

112
00:11:44,463 --> 00:11:48,318
My husband will have to come and will have to destroy this man.

113
00:11:49,912 --> 00:11:56,291
 When He will destroy him (Ravana), then I will go with Him."

114
00:11:56,532 --> 00:12:00,499
Hanumanji said, “That is okay!"

115
00:12:00,524 --> 00:12:03,263
 He could have picked Her up like that only.

116
00:12:03,581 --> 00:12:06,911
He had such powers.

117
00:12:07,301 --> 00:12:15,201
 But He said,"If Mother is saying so, it is okay."

118
00:12:15,434 --> 00:12:19,465
And after that, such a great war broke out.

119
00:12:19,490 --> 00:12:22,941
 There was a need for that.

120
00:12:24,849 --> 00:12:27,977
Now there were special qualities of Shri Ram.

121
00:12:28,002 --> 00:12:31,330
 Extremely powerful!

122
00:12:31,949 --> 00:12:35,754
And His aim would never go astray.

123
00:12:36,987 --> 00:12:41,997
 You must have heard what He did in Sita Swayamvar.

124
00:12:42,022 --> 00:12:44,767
But the same Shri Ram

125
00:12:44,792 --> 00:12:50,403
 when it was the case of Ravana

126
00:12:51,828 --> 00:12:54,017
 He didn't give up.

127
00:12:55,762 --> 00:12:57,884
He killed Him.

128
00:12:58,537 --> 00:13:06,128
 Tulsidas ji has given a beautiful description of this scene.

129
00:13:06,694 --> 00:13:12,677
Then Shri Ram was repeatedly hitting the arrows

130
00:13:14,914 --> 00:13:18,297
 at Ravana's ten heads.

131
00:13:18,456 --> 00:13:21,036
The heads would fall down one by one but get back again,

132
00:13:21,061 --> 00:13:22,871
 fall down and get back again.

133
00:13:26,137 --> 00:13:28,819
Then Laxman said ,"what are You doing?

134
00:13:29,185 --> 00:13:32,012
 Shoot one arrow in His heart,

135
00:13:32,834 --> 00:13:35,930
the moment You will hit an arrow in His heart

136
00:13:35,955 --> 00:13:37,605
 instantly He will die

137
00:13:37,630 --> 00:13:39,530
 Otherwise, how can He die ?

138
00:13:39,555 --> 00:13:41,406
He cannot die."

139
00:13:42,492 --> 00:13:47,025
 The arrow should hit His heart.

140
00:13:48,276 --> 00:13:52,231
There is a beautiful description of Shri Ram there.

141
00:13:52,653 --> 00:13:55,241
 He was a shy person, very shy.

142
00:13:55,415 --> 00:14:02,579
Shri Ram, even though He was so powerful, so intense

143
00:14:04,123 --> 00:14:06,625
 even though He was such a noble person

144
00:14:06,650 --> 00:14:09,846
 He said, " You see the problem is that

145
00:14:09,871 --> 00:14:14,818
 in Ravan's heart resides My Sita.

146
00:14:14,942 --> 00:14:17,336
So, I won't hit Him in his heart.

147
00:14:18,436 --> 00:14:22,281
 But when his head will cut off repeatedly

148
00:14:22,306 --> 00:14:26,620
 his attention will surely shift towards his head.

149
00:14:26,687 --> 00:14:30,532
At that time I will kill him with an arrow."

150
00:14:30,557 --> 00:14:32,519
 Otherwise for Him, it would be said

151
00:14:32,544 --> 00:14:35,030
that he would kill a person just with one arrow.

152
00:14:35,055 --> 00:14:37,882
 But now you see how delicate the matter is.

153
00:14:37,907 --> 00:14:44,411
Simply, it is a husband's love towards his wife.

154
00:14:45,615 --> 00:14:53,083
 Even though being an ocean of power, what an amount of love He had!

155
00:14:55,153 --> 00:14:58,688
There are many instances of Hanumanji

156
00:14:59,437 --> 00:15:10,934
 in which Hanumanji proved that He is ocean of love

157
00:15:11,110 --> 00:15:16,430
 and at the same time, he who is evil minded

158
00:15:16,526 --> 00:15:22,309
 he who bothers others, he who destroys others

159
00:15:22,756 --> 00:15:31,169
 he doesn't hesitate in any way to kill him.

160
00:15:31,969 --> 00:15:40,069
As all this fact is about Hanuman's devotion

161
00:15:40,460 --> 00:15:45,775
 the same is worth noticing about his power of strength.

162
00:15:48,545 --> 00:15:54,078
He knew that Ravana was afraid only of fire.

163
00:15:56,440 --> 00:15:59,506
 So, He went to Lanka and set it on fire.

164
00:16:00,014 --> 00:16:06,415
This was His power that He put Lanka on fire.

165
00:16:07,295 --> 00:16:13,341
 And in that fire, He didn't kill anyone, He did not burn anyone.

166
00:16:13,841 --> 00:16:16,484
Ravana also did not get burnt,  nobody got burnt

167
00:16:16,509 --> 00:16:19,525
 but he got scared.

168
00:16:19,550 --> 00:16:24,331
People got scared, as to what crime Ravana is doing.

169
00:16:24,553 --> 00:16:30,076
 People had given full consent about
 the type of deeds Ravana was doing.

170
00:16:30,282 --> 00:16:35,947
They would say, "He is Ravana. it is his will.

171
00:16:36,295 --> 00:16:41,319
 Whatever he wants to do, let him do. Who are we to question him?

172
00:16:41,899 --> 00:16:43,980
Ravana is after all Ravana."

173
00:16:45,445 --> 00:16:52,396
 But it is worth noticing that when Lanka was on fire

174
00:16:52,421 --> 00:16:56,570
 when Lanka was completely combusted

175
